  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nContinue the prototype work on the https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/7662 (attempt to construct it from the transaction) and implemented using RPC `wallet_getBalance` API in https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/7951\r\n\r\nInitial [Design](https://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?node-id=6455%3A122769)\r\n\r\n- The design is incomplete\r\n  - Short time intervals were dropped\r\n  - The cumulated balance based on selected networks is not shown\r\n\r\n### Specifications provided verbally by design\r\n\r\n- Fetch missing data every day or every 12 hours\r\n- Fetch in advance as soon as the app is shown so the user will have the balance data available when he reaches the graph\r\n- The precision and availability are lower priority than fetching costs\r\n  - We just need a general overview and snapping on specific periods doesn't matter\r\n- Save all the fetched data and add it to first time \"super-sync\"\r\n- We sum all the selected chains after we convert them into the reference fiat\r\n\r\n### Work packages\r\n\r\nLessons learned from the previous work\r\n\r\n- [x] #8226\r\n- [x] #8862\r\n  - See https://chainstack.com/ultimate-guide-erc20-token-balance/\r\n  - See `BalanceOf` ECR20 contract interface\r\n- [x] #8909\r\n- [x] #9205\r\n- [x] #9279\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- Fetching of historical balances is started on the first application start and runs in the background\r\n  - Can be checked using the Infura dashboard and watch for `eth_getBallance` count call increasing\r\n- Historical value balance is available to show as soon as it is retrieved for an account, in order\r\n- The balance is shown for selected networks in the user's preferred FIAT currency following the historical exchange rate",
